item.title: RscR V20 - Runescape Classic - Good Rates
item.dc:creator: @TheAlmightyKing TheAlmightyKing
item.description:
@TheAlmightyKing wrote:

imabeast:

@almightyking… please kid, any real rsc private server player knows your past and what you did, qq

Nothing has ever happened actually. The main things that did happen were, I had a mod and someone got access to his account somehow and some how knew the password to activate the mod commands. Then I demoted him.
I don’t know why people are saying this server has been up for the “11th” time either. When it was up once in 2008 while RscAngel was running and SwagPk. Once in 2009, I forget his name. But he hosted Piru or w/e. Took down almost every server, and I was paying about $350/Month just to keep it online and I couldn’t afford it since I only had about 60-90 players online. Then it’s up now. 2011-2012. (It was down for about 3 months in 2011).

It may seem like it’s been hosted more than it has since other people used my same server name to host their server to get more players.

It’s just hard to find people to actually trust with parts of your source/or with mod/staff rights these days in RSC. It seems like every mod you choose abuses some way or another. IE: Summon players to you, teleport players to other spots giving them an advantage and all of those things.

Also in your post if your pretty much referring to all the staff abuse there was, then I agree with you. I never abused or did anything myself because I wouldn’t want to lose players obviously. It’s just hard to find mods who won’t actually abuse somehow. But I have never infected/spread viruses to any of my players.
